The chairman of struggling South African state power firm Eskom, Jabu Mabuza, resigned on Friday after apologising for failing to meet a commitment to avoid power cuts during the December and January holiday period, the president’s office said. “In the wake of Mr Mabuza’s resignation, Government will soon announce a re-configured Eskom board with the appropriate mix of electricity industry, engineering and corporate governance experience,” the office of President Cyril Ramaphosa said in a statement. Below is the statement from the presidency: